</media><newline/>
In this case, the Lewis structure is inadequate to depict the fact that experimental studies have shown two unpaired electrons in each oxygen molecule<emphasis effect="italics">.</emphasis><newline/>
(b)<newline/><media id="fs-idm76406432" alt="A Lewis structure shows a carbon atom that is single bonded to two hydrogen atoms and double bonded to an oxygen atom. The oxygen atom has two lone pairs of electrons.">
