(j)<newline/><media id="fs-idm28530944" alt="A Lewis structure shows a carbon atom that is triple bonded to a nitrogen atom that has one lone pair of electrons. The carbon is also single bonded to a chlorine atom that has three lone pairs of electrons.">
<image mime-type="image/jpeg" src="../../media/CNX_Chem_07_03_Question7j_img.jpg"/>
