(k)<newline/><media id="fs-idm148703504" alt="A Lewis structure shows two carbon atoms joined with a triple bond. A superscripted 2 positive sign lies to the right of the second carbon.">
<image mime-type="image/jpeg" src="../../media/CNX_Chem_07_03_Question7k_img.jpg"/>
